# GitHub SSH Key Setup Guide

## 1. Generate SSH Key
```shell
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "melchi45@gmail.com"
```

Save location: /home/melchi45/.ssh/id_rsa_github
Passphrase: optional

```shell
Generating public/private rsa key pair.
Enter file in which to save the key (/home/melchi45/.ssh/id_rsa): /home/melchi45/.ssh/id_rsa_github
Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase):
Enter same passphrase again:
Your identification has been saved in /home/melchi45/.ssh/id_rsa_github
Your public key has been saved in /home/melchi45/.ssh/id_rsa_github.pub
The key fingerprint is:
SHA256:########################################### melchi45@gmail.com
The key's randomart image is:
+---[RSA 4096]----+
|      .=Bo .o+o+ |
|     .o==o .*=O o|
|      oo=. +oX.. |
|     . =  =o+o+  |
|      E S o=++.  |
|       . . +..o  |
|          . .o   |
|                 |
|                 |
+----[SHA256]-----+
```

## 2. View and Copy Public Key
```shell
cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
```
--- Copy the displayed key

## 3. Add SSH Key to GitHub

. Go to GitHub → top-right profile icon → Settings
. In the left sidebar, click SSH and GPG keys
. Click New SSH Key
  .. Title: any name you prefer
  .. Key: paste the public key you copied earlier

## 4. Test SSH Connection to GitHub
```shell
ssh -T git@github.com
```
If successful, you'll see:
```
Hi melchi45! You've successfully authenticated, but GitHub does not provide shell access.
```

## 5. Change GitHub Repository URL to SSH

```shell
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:melchi45/repository.git
```

예제:
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:melchi45/gdbserver_for_cross_compiler.git

## 6. git clone

```shell
git clone git@github.com:melchi45/utility.git
```
